# XI Elevated Design Reference

**Before implementing or modifying any UI**, consult the design reference image:

`ui:ux/WhatsApp Image 2026-06-11 at 23.40.54.jpeg`

This image is the **source of truth**. Match it pixel-perfectly. When the prompt and image conflict, follow the image.

## Brand Aesthetic

- Premium luxury outdoor dogwear — editorial, minimalist, high-end
- Monochrome palette: black backgrounds, white typography, light gray product surfaces
- Generous breathing room and editorial spacing — never cramped
- Clean sans-serif, uppercase headings with letter-spacing, restrained body text

## Key UI Patterns (from reference)

| Area | Spec |
|------|------|
| **Header** | Centered XI ELEVATED logo; hamburger left; search / account / cart right; transparent over hero |
| **Hero** | Full-bleed lifestyle photography; white uppercase headline; minimal CTA |
| **Product cards** | Light gray media bg; color name → type → price; no clutter |
| **Trust bar** | Light bg; icon + bold label + subtext columns |
| **Footer** | Black bg; 5 columns (brand, SHOP, INFO, SUPPORT, newsletter); underline email input + arrow submit; bottom bar: copyright left, social right |
| **Newsletter** | "JOIN THE PACK" heading; thin underline input; arrow submit |

## Implementation Rules

1. Read or re-check the reference image at the start of every UI phase or section build
2. Use existing `xi-*` snippets, design tokens (`xi-design-system.css`), and conventions
3. Do not delete Horizon files — replace active wiring via section groups and templates
4. Prefix all custom presentation files with `xi-`
5. Verify desktop, tablet, and mobile against the reference layout intent
